description: From un- +‎ live, as in alive.

verbs.description: unlive (third-person singular simple present unlives, present participle unliving, simple past and past participle unlived)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To bereave or deprive of life; make unalive.

verbs.description: unlive (third-person singular simple present unlives, present participle unliving, simple past and past participle unlived)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To undo having lived (a period of time) (for example, by living it in reverse), so that it ceases to have happened.
examples: I wish I could unlive the last ten years.
